.TH "RK\-TMUX\-BUFFER Reference" "" "" ""
.PP
Buffer is what \f[CR]tmux\f[R] calls the copy/paste locations.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]:choose\-buffer\f[R] / \f[CR]<prefix>=\f[R]: Paste from buffers
(e.g., clipboard history), the buffer name is listed here (e.g., as
\f[CR]buffer<number>\f[R])
.SH CLI
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]tmux save\-buffer \-\f[R] / \f[CR]tmux saveb \-\f[R]: Print the
contents of the default buffer to standard output (the \f[CR]\-\f[R] is
a required argument, this can also be a filename to save the buffer to)
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]tmux show\-buffer\f[R] / \f[CR]tmux showb\f[R]: Also prints the
contents of the default buffer, but breaks with some special characters
(e.g., accented letters)
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]tmux load\-buffer \-\f[R] / \f[CR]tmux loadb \-\f[R]: Save
standard input to the default buffer
.SS Flags
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\-b <buffer\-name>\f[R]: Specify a named buffer (e.g.,
\f[CR]buffer<number>\f[R])
